  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Expanding agribusiness and agro processing  to incentivise commercially oriented agriculltural production for food security, increased incomes and employment diversification in Burundi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A Dutch based company (Zazou ) group, having been requested by the ministry of agriculture in Burundi to support value chain development, approached UNIDO to partner in the development and implementation of an agro value chain development project.  The Sustainable Development Goals Partnership (SDGP) facility would fund the project,  a consortium of Dutch companies would invest in the processing (anchor) plant and UNIDO would play the role of Knowledge institution i.e. bringing in their global experience in value chain development and capacity building in the partnership.  The purpose of the project is to create employment diversification, and to contribute to food security and nutrition in Burundi by upgrading the horticulture sub sector.  The project seeks to provide technical assistance to the Government of Burundi to expand agribusiness and agro-processing as a way of creating a shift from the current subsistence to commercial agricultural production.  By building the capacities of producers towards a business oriented production, and improving the capacity for post harvest loss management, and increasing value addition the horticulture chain can play a pivotal role in improving the livelihoods of the target beneficiaries.   Further capacity building and optimization of all operations along the horticulture</narrative>
  </description>
